"Ha! You put me off, do you?" said our new visitor, taking a step forward and shaking his hunting-
crop. "I know you, you scoundrel!  I have heard of you before. You are Holmes, the meddler."

My friend smiled.

"Holmes, the busybody!"

His smile broadened.

"Holmes, the Scotland Yard Jack-in-office!"

Holmes chuckled heartily. "Your conversation is most entertaining," said he. "When you go out close
the door, for there is a decided draught."